kj8EJWCphe6KjE","type":0,"text":"Faint for [\"1d minutes\"/r 1d6], as per 18, and acquire a new -10-point Delusion, as per 22.","weight":1,"range":[26,26],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"modules/gurps-instant-defaults/img/icons/panic.png","rangeL":26,"rangeH":26},{"_id":"9MR14v1K6DksLtqw","type":0,"text":"Faint for [\"1d minutes\"/r 1d6], as per 18, and acquire a new -10-point mental disadvantage, as per 23.","weight":1,"range":[27,27],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"modules/gurps-instant-defaults/img/icons/panic.png","rangeL":27,"rangeH":27},{"_id":"xdi5MneCwYsIFeJc","type":0,"text":"Light coma. You fall unconscious, rolling vs. [\"HT\" /r [HT]] every 30 minutes to recover. For 6 hours after you come to, all skill rolls and attribute checks are at -2.","weight":1,"range":[28,28],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"modules/gurps-instant-defaults/img/icons/panic.png","rangeL":28,"rangeH":28},{"_id":"MAgA3sgN97uqpI7Q","type":0,"text":"Coma. As above, but you are unconscious for [\"1d hours\"/r 1d6]. Then roll vs. [\"HT\" /r [HT]]. If the roll fails, remain in a coma for another [\"1d hours\"/r 1d6], and so on.","weight":1,"range":[29,29],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"modules/gurps-instant-defaults/img/icons/panic.png","rangeL":29,"rangeH":29},{"_id":"MbA6pCechbRZR7DF","type":0,"text":"Catatonia. Stare into space for [\"1d days\"/r 1d6]. Then roll vs. [\"HT\" /r [HT]]. On a failed roll, remain catatonic for another [\"1d days\"/r 1d6], and so on. If you have no medical care, lose 1 HP the first day, 2 the second, and so on. If you survive and awaken, all skill rolls and attribute checks are at -2 for as many days as the catatonia lasted.","weight":1,"range":[30,30],"drawn":false,"flags":{},"img":"modules/gurps-instant-defaults/img/icons/panic.png","rangeL":30,"rangeH":30},{"_id":"2rQeetZ4zMssV6MD","type":0,"text":"Seizure. You lose control of your body and fall to the ground in a fit lasting [\"1d minutes\"/r 1d6] and costing [\"1d FP\"/r 1d6]. Also, roll vs. [\"HT\" /r 